{
  "text": "Several studies suggest a role for at least some of the MCRs in cancer development. An association between MC1R and PCa risk was reported in human [CITATION_1] and central MCR blockade with SHU9119-reversed PCa anorexia in Wistar rats [CITATION_2] . Additionally, MC5R is widely expressed in normal rodent exocrine glands including the prostate [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14051546",
